This is probably my first map that I actually put a lot of work into. Took about 1-2 weeks to make. There's only 1 bug, which doesn't really get in the way of gameplay, which is the roof. If you ever notice, the roof may look a bit strange. For some reason, in Hammer, I try to use the vertex editor to shape the brushes into a roof, but whenever I compile the map or launch hammer again, some of the brushes go back into a cube, so some parts of the roof look a bit strange. Oh, and try not to fall in the water, because there's no way out.

Enjoy.

CS_REALMANSION_BETA-HDR - Hostage Rescue by [HYBRID] aka LUNATIC With the help of SHEEPRIDER THIS MAP IS DEVOTED TO FPSBANANA AND ARKANA (HYBRID'S LOVELY WIFE) Okay this is my first map and first of all try's in mapmaking. So try to don't judge hard. This map is an remake of very-very old CS 1 map - CS_MANSION. This map was first map for CS1, and it was the prototype for CS_ESTATE. In CSS, some guy remaked CS_ESTATE, but he give to his map name of CS_MANSION. So anyway, original mansion was my first map i start playing CS ) I remember that times, i haven't own PC yet, and play SEGA MEGADRIVE and Sony PS1... My friend tells me "in our cybercafes was out new pwning game - COUNTER-STRIKE! And we go to the club and when we get inside everyone has played CS) the map was CS_MANSION. I start play and i don't know even how to buy weapons, how to move, i just stay in hostages room and every round got pwned by others. And i say that day "Omg this map and this game is most amazing game I've ever played!" So, when CSS is out, i start searching sites and servers for this old cs_mansion, but have no luck. I don't know why but no one makes this map for CSS yet. So I do this. Howewer, this is the BETA. I didnt'm make cameras for ct spawn, and there is only pregenerated .nav meshes, so bot's don't use watercanal and ladder yet. But i'll fix it, when i'll have time. So, enjoy the map! I think you'll like it! It's a kind of nostalgie for me) FEATURES: - Supporting High Dynamic Range - HDR - 64 spawnpoints - 3 hostages, working lightswitches - A LOT OF FUN AND COOL GAMEPLAY [Hybrid] aka Lunatic: Level Geomety / Texturing / Design / Waypoints Sheeprider (The great man and a good mapper who helps me with my map): Builing Cubemaps / HDR Lighting / Map Compiling / Bug Fixes Other credits are belong to Valve and original authors of cs_mansion SPECIAL THANK TO: all FPSB community for providing tutorials and giving advices! It is the best FPS Customization site with the best and friendly people from all whom I ever saw! If you want to change or redone map please write to my e-mail: hy8r1d@mail.ru HERE IS SOME ADDITIONAL SCREENSHOTS: and some announce: FINAL version will come with advanced waypoints, camera for CT spawn, additional details and some bug fixes) ENJOY

This is yet another recreation of the popular map cs_crackhouse. This version is based on the CS:S version, not the original CS 1.6 version as I've never played it.

All of the other recreations have some little quirk in them I did not like. I did not like the day lighting, alternate routes or portions added in, or they just edited the decompiled original map to make it look better. This is a complete recreation from scratch, using measurements from the original (rounded to the nearest power of 2, of course).

I believe this is the first crackhouse map to use HDR, so that should be a big plus. The bots only get stuck on the rarest of occasions, due to me editing the nav. Place names, overviews, more detail, soundscapes, etc. Basically, this is what cs_crackhouse SHOULD have been, if it had been made better.

Anyway, hope you enjoy!

During a visit to the pyramid by the Egyptian president and the Minister for Tourism a local militant group attacked the pyramid, killed the bodyguards and took two politicians hostage. Special forces were dropped off with a mission to rescue President and Minister alive and destroy the Terrorists.

Counter Terrorists : Breach the house and eliminate the threat. Terrorists: Repel the CT assault!
Backstory: Mapped after my old house this map plays off a terrorist stand off, where they hold out in my former home. Polish Hostage comes from a line in SWAT the movie, where man, doing the same thing, hides out in his house armed with a shotgun threatening the police. Samuel L. Jackson calls him a "Polish Hostage". Counter Terrorists must break the house and eliminate any and all threats. There are many parts of the map that are destructible, making the entry points of rooms and the house itself, much more than just doors and windows. Notes: This is just a beta version of the map. I'm working tirelessly on trying to make the breakable parts of the wall seem non-existant or just another regular part of the wall. Any suggestions would be awesome. thanks.
